# ReactJS Coding Rules

## General
- Correctness and clarity over speed. Accessibility is required.
- Comments only explain *why*, never *what*.
- Add to existing files before creating new ones.
- No generic names like `index.tsx` ‚Äî use explicit names like `UserProfile.tsx`.
- No abbreviated variable names (`error` not `err`, `button` not `btn`).

## File Naming
| Type | Convention |
|------|-----------|
| Component / Page | `PascalCase.tsx` |
| Hook | `use-kebab-case.ts` |
| Service | `kebab-case.service.ts` |
| Store | `kebab-case.store.ts` |
| Schema | `kebab-case.schema.ts` |
| Types | `kebab-case.types.ts` |

## Exports
- **Next.js route files** (`app/.../page.tsx`): Default Export only ‚Äî thin wrapper, no logic.
- **Feature page components** (`features/.../pages/`): Named Export.
- **Everything else**: Named Export.

## Folder Structure
```
src/features/<feature>/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pages/                    # Page orchestrators: data fetching, state, navigation
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts              # Re-exports all page components
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ LoginPage.tsx         # Named export; calls hooks, owns business logic
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <PageName>/           # Sub-components scoped to that page (UI only, receive props)
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts          # Re-exports all sub-components in this folder
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ LoginForm.tsx     # No direct API calls; all data via props
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/                    # React Query hooks (use-kebab-case.ts)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ services/                 # Axios wrappers as plain objects (kebab-case.service.ts)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ schemas/                  # Zod schemas (kebab-case.schema.ts)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ types/                    # TypeScript types (kebab-case.types.ts)
```

**Page orchestrators** (`pages/`) own: mutations/queries, form submission handlers, navigation, global state writes. Named exports. Always add to `pages/index.ts`.

**Page sub-components** (`components/<PageName>/`) are UI-only: receive data and callbacks via props, no direct hook/service calls except when isolated logic demands it (e.g. a self-contained query widget). Named exports. Always add to `components/<PageName>/index.ts`.

**Imports**: Always import from the folder index, not individual files ‚Äî `from '../components/LoginPage'` not `from '../components/LoginPage/LoginForm'`.

**Next.js route files** (`app/.../page.tsx`) are thin wrappers ‚Äî default export, no business logic, just `return <FeaturePage />` or passes route params as props.

**shadcn/ui is mandatory.** Always use primitives from `src/components/ui/` first. Never build custom div-only controls when an accessible shadcn component exists. If the needed component is missing, install it via the shadcn CLI before writing a custom replacement.
Zustand stores ‚Üí `src/stores/`
App-wide config constants (roles, permissions, etc.) ‚Üí `src/config/`

**Roles**: `src/config/roles.ts` is the single source of truth for `UserRole` type and `USER_ROLES` constant. Never redefine roles elsewhere ‚Äî always import from `@/config/roles`.

## Error Handling
- Never swallow errors silently.
- Always: `console.error(error)` + `toast.error('...')` via Sonner.
- All async operations handle 3 states: `loading`, `error`, `success`.
- Use early returns for loading/error to keep render clean.

## State
- Never mutate state directly ‚Äî use immutable setter patterns.
- Minimize `useEffect`. Derive state during render when possible.
- `useEffect` with subscriptions/timers must return a cleanup function.

## State Management
- **Client/UI state** (auth, preferences, UI flags) ‚Üí Zustand in `src/stores/`.
- **Server state** (API data) ‚Üí React Query. Never store server data in Zustand.
- React Query hooks live in `features/<feature>/hooks/`.
- Query keys must be arrays: `['resource', params]`.
- Always handle `onError` in mutations.

## Service Layer
- Services are plain objects, not classes.
- Import Axios instance from `src/lib/axios.ts` as `api`.
- Return unwrapped `r.data`, not the full Axios response.
- Do not catch errors in services ‚Äî let React Query handle them.

## Forms
- Use React Hook Form + Zod. Define Zod schema first, infer TS type from it.
- No manual validation logic when Zod can express it.
- Field errors from `form.formState.errors`, not global state.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only. Class order: layout ‚Üí spacing ‚Üí typography ‚Üí colors ‚Üí states.
- Conditional/merged classes always use `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts`.
- Component variants use CVA (`class-variance-authority`).
- Do not manually reorder Tailwind classes ‚Äî `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss` handles it.

## TypeScript
- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow the type, or define a proper type.
- No type assertions (`as SomeType`) unless unavoidable ‚Äî add a comment explaining why.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections/aliases.
- Derive types from source of truth ‚Äî never duplicate: use `z.infer<>` from Zod schemas, `ReturnType<>`, `Parameters<>`, `Awaited<>` when applicable.
- Use `type` keyword for type-only imports: `import type { Task } from '../types/task.types'`.
- Mark optional props explicitly with `?`. Never use `| undefined` manually when `?` suffices.
- Use `readonly` for props/state that should not be mutated.
- Avoid enums ‚Äî use `as const` objects or Zod `z.enum()` instead.

## Component Props
- Explicit TypeScript interfaces for all props. No `any`.
- Destructure props in function signature.
- Type-only imports use `import type { ... }`.

## Routing
- Lazy routes wrapped in `<Suspense fallback={<Spinner />}>`.
- Protected routes use `ProtectedRoute` (checks `useAuthStore`).
- `useNavigate` only inside components or hooks, never in services.
